# Vecinita operator secrets — MASTER TEMPLATE (placeholders only)
#
# Copy to repo-root prod.env (gitignored) and fill in real values:
#   cp prod.env.example prod.env
#
# NEVER commit prod.env or real secrets to git.
#
# Per-platform templates (copy the relevant sections into prod.env):
#   infra/github/.env.example      → GitHub Actions encrypted secrets
#   infra/do/.env.example          → DigitalOcean App Platform (4 apps)
#   infra/modal/.env.example       → Modal secret vecinita-data-management
#   supabase/.env.example          → Supabase CLI (link, config push, db push)
#   infra/resend/.env.example      → Resend API key + verified sender (3-way sync)
#   infra/staging/.env.example     → Operator smoke / connectivity (H1–H5)
#
# One-shot sync to every environment:
#   set -a && source prod.env && set +a
#   export DIGITALOCEAN_TOKEN='dop_v1_...'
#   bash scripts/deploy/sync_env.sh --apply
#
# Matrix: docs/staging-secrets-matrix.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Include all sections below by merging the per-platform .env.example files,
# or source them in order (later files override earlier keys):
#
#   set -a
#   source infra/github/.env.example    # fill placeholders first
#   source infra/do/.env.example
#   source infra/modal/.env.example
#   source supabase/.env.example
#   source infra/resend/.env.example
#   set +a
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# See infra/github/.env.example for the full canonical key list used by CI/CD.
